  210. /* Switch from OCaml to C stack. */
  211. .macro SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  212.     /* Fill in Caml_state->current_stack->sp */
  213.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(current_stack)
  214.         mov     TMP2, sp
  215.         str     TMP2, Stack_sp(TMP)
  216.     /* Fill in Caml_state->c_stack */
  217.         ldr     TMP2, Caml_state(c_stack)
  218.         str     TMP, Cstack_stack(TMP2)
  219.         mov     TMP, sp
  220.         str     TMP, Cstack_sp(TMP2)
  221.     /* Switch to C stack */
  222.         mov     sp, TMP2
  223. #ifdef ASM_CFI_SUPPORTED
  224.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  225.     /* sp  points to the c_stack_link. */
  226.         .cfi_escape DW_CFA_def_cfa_expression, 5,                 \
  227.            DW_OP_breg + DW_REG_sp, Cstack_sp_offset, DW_OP_deref, \
  228.            DW_OP_plus_uconst, 16 /* fp + retaddr */
  229. #endif
  230. .endm

  232. /* Switch from C to OCaml stack. */
  233. .macro SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  234.         ldr     TMP, Cstack_sp(sp)
  235.         mov     sp, TMP
  236.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  237. .endm

  239. /* Save all of the registers that may be in use to a free gc_regs bucket
  240.    and store ALLOC_PTR and TRAP_PTR back to Caml_state
  241.    At the end the saved registers are placed in Caml_state(gc_regs)
  242. */
  243. .macro SAVE_ALL_REGS
  244.     /* First, save the young_ptr & exn_handler */
  245.         str     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  246.         str     TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  247.     /* Now, use TMP to point to the gc_regs bucket */
  248.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  249.         ldr     TMP2, [TMP, 0] /* next ptr */
  250.         str     TMP2, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  251.     /* Save allocatable registers */
  252.         stp     x0, x1, [TMP, 16]
  253.         stp     x2, x3, [TMP, 32]
  254.         stp     x4, x5, [TMP, 48]
  255.         stp     x6, x7, [TMP, 64]
  256.         stp     x8, x9, [TMP, 80]
  257.         stp     x10, x11, [TMP, 96]
  258.         stp     x12, x13, [TMP, 112]
  259.         stp     x14, x15, [TMP, 128]
  260.         stp     x19, x20, [TMP, 144]
  261.         stp     x21, x22, [TMP, 160]
  262.         stp     x23, x24, [TMP, 176]
  263.         str     x25, [TMP, 192]
  264.     /* Save caller-save floating-point registers
  265.        (callee-saves are preserved by C functions) */
  266.         stp     d0, d1, [TMP, 208]
  267.         stp     d2, d3, [TMP, 224]
  268.         stp     d4, d5, [TMP, 240]
  269.         stp     d6, d7, [TMP, 256]
  270.         stp     d16, d17, [TMP, 272]
  271.         stp     d18, d19, [TMP, 288]
  272.         stp     d20, d21, [TMP, 304]
  273.         stp     d22, d23, [TMP, 320]
  274.         stp     d24, d25, [TMP, 336]
  275.         stp     d26, d27, [TMP, 352]
  276.         stp     d28, d29, [TMP, 368]
  277.         stp     d30, d31, [TMP, 384]
  278.         add     TMP, TMP, #16
  279.         str     TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  280. .endm

  282. /* Undo SAVE_ALL_REGS by loading the registers saved in Caml_state(gc_regs)
  283.    and refreshing ALLOC_PTR & TRAP_PTR from Caml_state */
  284. .macro RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  285.     /* Restore x0, x1, freeing up the next ptr slot */
  286.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  287.         sub     TMP, TMP, #16
  288.     /* Restore registers */
  289.         ldp     x0, x1, [TMP, 16]
  290.         ldp     x2, x3, [TMP, 32]
  291.         ldp     x4, x5, [TMP, 48]
  292.         ldp     x6, x7, [TMP, 64]
  293.         ldp     x8, x9, [TMP, 80]
  294.         ldp     x10, x11, [TMP, 96]
  295.         ldp     x12, x13, [TMP, 112]
  296.         ldp     x14, x15, [TMP, 128]
  297.         ldp     x19, x20, [TMP, 144]
  298.         ldp     x21, x22, [TMP, 160]
  299.         ldp     x23, x24, [TMP, 176]
  300.         ldr     x25, [TMP, 192]
  301.         ldp     d0, d1, [TMP, 208]
  302.         ldp     d2, d3, [TMP, 224]
  303.         ldp     d4, d5, [TMP, 240]
  304.         ldp     d6, d7, [TMP, 256]
  305.         ldp     d16, d17, [TMP, 272]
  306.         ldp     d18, d19, [TMP, 288]
  307.         ldp     d20, d21, [TMP, 304]
  308.         ldp     d22, d23, [TMP, 320]
  309.         ldp     d24, d25, [TMP, 336]
  310.         ldp     d26, d27, [TMP, 352]
  311.         ldp     d28, d29, [TMP, 368]
  312.         ldp     d30, d31, [TMP, 384]
  313.     /* Put gc_regs struct back in bucket linked list */
  314.         ldr     TMP2, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  315.         str     TMP2, [TMP, 0]  /* next ptr */
  316.         str     TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  317.     /* Reload new allocation pointer & exn handler */
  318.         ldr     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  319.         ldr     TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  320. .endm

  327. FUNCTION(caml_call_realloc_stack)
  328.         CFI_STARTPROC
  329.     /* Save return address and frame pointer */
  330.         CFI_OFFSET(29, -16)
  331.         CFI_OFFSET(30, -8)
  332.         stp     x29, x30, [sp, -16]!
  333.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  334.         add     x29, sp, #0
  335.     /* Save all registers (including ALLOC_PTR & TRAP_PTR) */
  336.         SAVE_ALL_REGS
  337.         ldr     C_ARG_1, [sp, 16] /* argument */
  338.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  339.         bl      G(caml_try_realloc_stack)
  340.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  341.         cbz     x0, 1f
  342.         RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  343.     /* Free stack space and return to caller */
  344.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  345.         ret
  346. 1:      RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  347.     /* Raise the Stack_overflow exception */
  348.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  349.         add     sp, sp, 16 /* pop argument */
  350.         ADDRGLOBAL(x0, caml_exn_Stack_overflow)
  351.         b       G(caml_raise_exn)
  352.         CFI_ENDPROC
  353.         END_FUNCTION(caml_call_realloc_stack)

  355. FUNCTION(caml_call_gc)
  356.         CFI_STARTPROC
  357. L(caml_call_gc):
  358.     /* Save return address and frame pointer */
  359.         CFI_OFFSET(29, -16)
  360.         CFI_OFFSET(30, -8)
  361.         stp     x29, x30, [sp, -16]!
  362.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  363.         add     x29, sp, #0
  364.     /* Store all registers (including ALLOC_PTR & TRAP_PTR) */
  365.         SAVE_ALL_REGS
  366.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  367.     /* Call the garbage collector */
  368.         bl      G(caml_garbage_collection)
  369.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  370.         RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  371.     /* Free stack space and return to caller */
  372.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  373.         ret
  374.         CFI_ENDPROC
  375.         END_FUNCTION(caml_call_gc)

  428.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  429.     /* Make the exception handler alloc ptr available to the C code */
  430.         str     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  431.         str     TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  432.     /* Call the function */
  433.         blr     ADDITIONAL_ARG
  434.     /* Reload alloc ptr  */
  435.         ldr     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  436.     /* Load ocaml stack */
  437.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  438.     /* Return */
  439.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  440.         ret
  441.         CFI_ENDPROC
  442.         END_FUNCTION(caml_c_call)

  444. FUNCTION(caml_c_call_stack_args)
  445.         CFI_STARTPROC
  446.     /* Arguments:
  447.         C arguments  : x0 to x7, d0 to d7
  448.         C function   : ADDITIONAL_ARG
  449.         C stack args : begin=STACK_ARG_BEGIN
  450.                        end=STACK_ARG_END */
  451.         CFI_OFFSET(29, -16)
  452.         CFI_OFFSET(30, -8)
  453.         stp     x29, x30, [sp, -16]!
  454.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  455.         add     x29, sp, #0
  456.     /* Switch from OCaml to C */
  457.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  458.     /* Make the exception handler alloc ptr available to the C code */
  459.         str     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  460.         str     TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  461.     /* Store sp to restore after call */
  462.         mov     x19, sp
  463.     /* Copy arguments from OCaml to C stack
  464.        NB: STACK_ARG_{BEGIN,END} are 16-byte aligned */
  465. 1:      sub     STACK_ARG_END, STACK_ARG_END, 16
  466.         cmp     STACK_ARG_END, STACK_ARG_BEGIN
  467.         b.lo    2f
  468.         ldp     TMP, TMP2, [STACK_ARG_END]
  469.         stp     TMP, TMP2, [sp, -16]!; CFI_ADJUST(16)
  470.         b       1b
  471. 2:  /* Call the function */
  472.         blr     ADDITIONAL_ARG
  473.     /* Restore stack */
  474.         mov     sp, x19
  475.     /* Reload alloc ptr */
  476.         ldr     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  477.     /* Switch from C to OCaml */
  478.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  479.     /* Return */
  480.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  481.         ret
  482. CFI_ENDPROC

  484. /* Start the OCaml program */

  486. FUNCTION(caml_start_program)
  487.         CFI_STARTPROC
  488.     /* domain state is passed as arg from C */
  489.         mov     TMP, C_ARG_1
  490.         ADDRGLOBAL(TMP2, caml_program)

  492. /* Code shared with caml_callback* */
  493. /* Address of domain state is in TMP */
  494. /* Address of OCaml code to call is in TMP2 */
  495. /* Arguments to the OCaml code are in x0...x7 */

  497. L(jump_to_caml):
  498.     /* Set up stack frame and save callee-save registers */
  499.         CFI_OFFSET(29, -160)
  500.         CFI_OFFSET(30, -152)
  501.         stp     x29, x30, [sp, -160]!
  502.         CFI_ADJUST(160)
  503.         add     x29, sp, #0
  504.         stp     x19, x20, [sp, 16]
  505.         stp     x21, x22, [sp, 32]
  506.         stp     x23, x24, [sp, 48]
  507.         stp     x25, x26, [sp, 64]
  508.         stp     x27, x28, [sp, 80]
  509.         stp     d8, d9, [sp, 96]
  510.         stp     d10, d11, [sp, 112]
  511.         stp     d12, d13, [sp, 128]
  512.         stp     d14, d15, [sp, 144]
  513.     /* Load domain state pointer from argument */
  514.         mov     DOMAIN_STATE_PTR, TMP
  515.     /* Reload allocation pointer */
  516.         ldr     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  517.     /* Build (16-byte aligned) struct c_stack_link on the C stack */
  518.         ldr     x8, Caml_state(c_stack)
  519.         stp     x8, xzr, [sp, -16]! /* C_stack_prev, pad */
  520.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  521.         stp     xzr, xzr, [sp, -16]! /* C_stack_stack, C_stack_sp */
  522.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  523.         mov     x8, sp
  524.         str     x8, Caml_state(c_stack)
  525.     /* Load the OCaml stack */
  526.         ldr     x8, Caml_state(current_stack)
  527.         ldr     x8, Stack_sp(x8)
  528.     /* Store the gc_regs for callbacks during a GC */
  529.         ldr     x9, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  530.         str     x9, [x8, -8]!
  531.     /* Store the stack pointer to allow DWARF unwind */
  532.         mov     x9, sp
  533.         str     x9, [x8, -8]! /* C_stack_sp */
  534.     /* Setup a trap frame to catch exceptions escaping the OCaml code */
  535.         ldr     x9, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  536.         adr     x10, L(trap_handler)
  537.         stp     x9, x10, [x8, -16]!
  538.         mov     TRAP_PTR, x8
  539.     /* Switch stacks and call the OCaml code */
  540.         mov     sp, x8
  541. #ifdef ASM_CFI_SUPPORTED
  542.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  543.         .cfi_escape DW_CFA_def_cfa_expression, 3 + 2 + 2,             \
  544.             /* sp points to the exn handler on the OCaml stack */     \
  545.             /* sp + 16 contains the C_STACK_SP */                     \
  546.           DW_OP_breg + DW_REG_sp, 16 /* exn handler */, DW_OP_deref,  \
  547.             /* 32   struct c_stack_link + pad */                      \
  548.             /* 18*8 callee save regs */                               \
  549.             /* 16   fp + ret addr */                                  \
  550.             /* need to split to get under 127 limit */                \
  551.           DW_OP_plus_uconst, 96, DW_OP_plus_uconst, 96
  552. #endif
  553.     /* Call the OCaml code */
  554.         blr     TMP2
  555. L(caml_retaddr):
  556.     /* Pop the trap frame, restoring Caml_state->exn_handler */
  557.         ldr     x8, [sp], 16
  558.         CFI_ADJUST(-16)
  559.         str     x8, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  560. L(return_result):
  561.     /* restore GC regs */
  562.         ldp     x8, x9, [sp], 16
  563.         CFI_ADJUST(-16)
  564.         str     x9, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  565.     /* Update allocation pointer */
  566.         str     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  567.     /* Return to C stack */
  568.         ldr     x8, Caml_state(current_stack)
  569.         mov     x9, sp
  570.         str     x9, Stack_sp(x8)
  571.         ldr     x9, Caml_state(c_stack)
  572.         mov     sp, x9
  573.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  574.     /* Pop the struct c_stack_link */
  575.         ldr     x8, Cstack_prev(sp)
  576.         add     sp, sp, 32
  577.         CFI_ADJUST(-32)
  578.         str     x8, Caml_state(c_stack)
  579.     /* Reload callee-save registers and return address */
  580.         ldp     x19, x20, [sp, 16]
  581.         ldp     x21, x22, [sp, 32]
  582.         ldp     x23, x24, [sp, 48]
  583.         ldp     x25, x26, [sp, 64]
  584.         ldp     x27, x28, [sp, 80]
  585.         ldp     d8, d9, [sp, 96]
  586.         ldp     d10, d11, [sp, 112]
  587.         ldp     d12, d13, [sp, 128]
  588.         ldp     d14, d15, [sp, 144]
  589.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 160
  590.         CFI_ADJUST(-160)
  591.     /* Return to C caller */
  592.         ret
  593.         CFI_ENDPROC
  594.         END_FUNCTION(caml_start_program)

  596. /* The trap handler */

  598.         .align  2
  599. L(trap_handler):
  600.         CFI_STARTPROC
  601.     /* Save exception pointer */
  602.         str     TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  603.     /* Encode exception bucket as an exception result */
  604.         orr     x0, x0, #2
  605.     /* Return it */
  606.         b       L(return_result)
  607.         CFI_ENDPROC

  609. /* Exceptions */

  611. .macro JUMP_TO_TRAP_PTR
  612.     /* Cut stack at current trap handler */
  613.         mov     sp, TRAP_PTR
  614.     /* Pop previous handler and jump to it */
  615.         ldr     TMP, [sp, 8]
  616.         ldr     TRAP_PTR, [sp], 16
  617.         br      TMP
  618. .endm

  620. /* Raise an exception from OCaml */
  621. FUNCTION(caml_raise_exn)
  622.         CFI_STARTPROC
  623.     /* Test if backtrace is active */
  624.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(backtrace_active)
  625.         cbnz    TMP, 2f
  626. 1:
  627.         JUMP_TO_TRAP_PTR
  628. 2:  /* Zero backtrace_pos */
  629.         str     xzr, Caml_state(backtrace_pos)
  630. L(caml_reraise_exn_stash):
  631.     /* Preserve exception bucket in callee-save register x19 */
  632.         mov     x19, x0
  633.     /* Stash the backtrace */
  634.                                /* arg1: exn bucket, already in x0 */
  635.         mov     x1, x30        /* arg2: pc of raise */
  636.         mov     x2, sp         /* arg3: sp of raise */
  637.         mov     x3, TRAP_PTR   /* arg4: sp of handler */
  638.     /* Switch to C stack */
  639.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(c_stack)
  640.         mov     sp, TMP
  641.         bl      G(caml_stash_backtrace)
  642.     /* Restore exception bucket and raise */
  643.         mov     x0, x19
  644.         b       1b
  645.         CFI_ENDPROC
  646.         END_FUNCTION(caml_raise_exn)

  648. FUNCTION(caml_reraise_exn)
  649.         CFI_STARTPROC
  650.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(backtrace_active)
  651.         cbnz    TMP, L(caml_reraise_exn_stash)
  652.         JUMP_TO_TRAP_PTR
  653.         CFI_ENDPROC
  654.         END_FUNCTION(caml_reraise_exn)

  656. /* Raise an exception from C */

  658. FUNCTION(caml_raise_exception)
  659.         CFI_STARTPROC
  660.     /* Load the domain state ptr */
  661.         mov     DOMAIN_STATE_PTR, C_ARG_1
  662.     /* Load the exception bucket */
  663.         mov     x0, C_ARG_2
  664.     /* Reload trap ptr and alloc ptr */
  665.         ldr     TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  666.         ldr     ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  667.     /* Discard the C stack pointer and reset to ocaml stack */
  668.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(current_stack)
  669.         ldr     TMP, Stack_sp(TMP)
  670.         mov     sp, TMP
  671.     /* Restore frame and link on return to OCaml */
  672.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  673.         b       G(caml_raise_exn)
  674.         CFI_ENDPROC
  675.         END_FUNCTION(caml_raise_exception)

  677. /* Callback from C to OCaml */

  679. FUNCTION(caml_callback_asm)
  680.         CFI_STARTPROC
  681.     /* Initial shuffling of arguments */
  682.     /* (x0 = Caml_state, x1 = closure, [x2] = first arg) */
  683.         mov     TMP, x0
  684.         ldr     x0, [x2]        /* x0 = first arg */
  685.                                 /* x1 = closure environment */
  686.         ldr     TMP2, [x1]       /* code pointer */
  687.         b       L(jump_to_caml)
  688.         CFI_ENDPROC
  689.         END_FUNCTION(caml_callback_asm)

  691. FUNCTION(caml_callback2_asm)
  692.         CFI_STARTPROC
  693.     /* Initial shuffling of arguments */
  694.     /* (x0 = Caml_state, x1 = closure, [x2] = arg1, [x2,8] = arg2) */
  695.         mov     TMP, x0
  696.         mov     TMP2, x1
  697.         ldp     x0, x1, [x2, 0] /* x0 = first arg, x1 = second arg */
  698.         mov     x2, TMP2         /* x2 = closure environment */
  699.         ADDRGLOBAL(TMP2, caml_apply2)
  700.         b       L(jump_to_caml)
  701.         CFI_ENDPROC
  702.         END_FUNCTION(caml_callback2_asm)

  704. FUNCTION(caml_callback3_asm)
  705.         CFI_STARTPROC
  706.     /* Initial shuffling of arguments */
  707.     /* (x0 = Caml_state, x1 = closure, [x2] = arg1, [x2,8] = arg2,
  708.         [x2,16] = arg3) */
  709.         mov     TMP, x0
  710.         mov     x3, x1          /* x3 = closure environment */
  711.         ldp     x0, x1, [x2, 0] /* x0 = first arg, x1 = second arg */
  712.         ldr     x2, [x2, 16]    /* x2 = third arg */
  713.         ADDRGLOBAL(TMP2, caml_apply3)
  714.         b       L(jump_to_caml)
  715.         CFI_ENDPROC
  716.         END_FUNCTION(caml_callback3_asm)

  718. /* Fibers */

  720. /* Switch between OCaml stacks. Clobbers TMP and switches TRAP_PTR
  721.    Preserves old_stack and new_stack registers */
  722. .macro SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS old_stack, new_stack
  723.     /* Save frame pointer and return address for old_stack */
  724.         stp     x29, x30, [sp, -16]!
  725.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  726.         add     x29, sp, #0
  727.     /* Save OCaml SP and exn_handler in the stack info */
  728.         mov     TMP, sp
  729.         str     TMP, Stack_sp(\old_stack)
  730.         str     TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(\old_stack)
  731.     /* switch stacks */
  732.         str     \new_stack, Caml_state(current_stack)
  733.         ldr     TMP, Stack_sp(\new_stack)
  734.         mov     sp, TMP
  735.     /* restore exn_handler for new stack */
  736.         ldr     TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(\new_stack)
  737.     /* Restore frame pointer and return address for new_stack */
  738.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  739. .endm


  742. /*
  743. * A continuation is a one word object that points to a fiber. A fiber [f] will
  744. * point to its parent at Handler_parent(Stack_handler(f)). In the following,
  745. * the [last_fiber] refers to the last fiber in the linked-list formed by the
  746. * parent pointer.
  747. */

  749. FUNCTION(caml_perform)
  750.         CFI_STARTPROC
  751.     /*  x0: effect to perform
  752.         x1: freshly allocated continuation */
  753.         ldr     x2, Caml_state(current_stack) /* x2 := old stack */
  754.         add     x3, x2, 1 /* x3 := Val_ptr(old stack) */
  755.         str     x3, [x1] /* Iniitalize continuation */
  756. L(do_perform):
  757.     /*  x0: effect to perform
  758.         x1: continuation
  759.         x2: old_stack
  760.         x3: last_fiber */

  762.         ldr     x9, Stack_handler(x2)  /* x9 := old stack -> handler */
  763.         ldr     x10, Handler_parent(x9) /* x10 := parent stack */
  764.         cbz     x10, 1f
  765.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS x2, x10
  766.     /*  we have to null the Handler_parent after the switch because
  767.         the Handler_parent is needed to unwind the stack for backtraces */
  768.         str     xzr, Handler_parent(x9) /* Set parent of performer to NULL */
  769.         ldr     TMP, Handler_effect(x9)
  770.         mov     x2, x3                 /* x2 := last_fiber */
  771.         mov     x3, TMP                /* x3 := effect handler */
  772.         b       G(caml_apply3)
  773. 1:
  774.     /*  switch back to original performer before raising Effect.Unhandled
  775.         (no-op unless this is a reperform) */
  776.         ldr     x10, [x1] /* load performer stack from continuation */
  777.         sub     x10, x10, 1 /* x10 := Ptr_val(x10) */
  778.         ldr     x9, Caml_state(current_stack)
  779.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS x9, x10
  780.     /*  No parent stack. Raise Effect.Unhandled. */
  781.         ADDRGLOBAL(ADDITIONAL_ARG, caml_raise_unhandled_effect)
  782.         b       G(caml_c_call)
  783.         CFI_ENDPROC
  784.         END_FUNCTION(caml_perform)

  786. FUNCTION(caml_reperform)
  787.         CFI_STARTPROC
  788.     /*  x0: effect to perform
  789.         x1: continuation
  790.         x2: last_fiber */
  791.         ldr     TMP, Stack_handler_from_cont(x2)
  792.         ldr     x2, Caml_state(current_stack) /* x2 := old stack */
  793.         str     x2, Handler_parent(TMP) /* Append to last_fiber */
  794.         add     x3, x2, 1 /* x3 (last_fiber) := Val_ptr(old stack) */
  795.         b       L(do_perform)
  796.         CFI_ENDPROC
  797.         END_FUNCTION(caml_reperform)

  799. FUNCTION(caml_resume)
  800. CFI_STARTPROC
  801.     /*  x0: new fiber
  802.         x1: fun
  803.         x2: arg */
  804.         sub     x0, x0, 1 /* x0 = Ptr_val(x0) */
  805.         ldr     x3, [x1]  /* code pointer */
  806.     /* Check if stack null, then already used */
  807.         cbz     x0, 2f
  808.     /* Find end of list of stacks (put in x8) */
  809.         mov     TMP, x0
  810. 1:      ldr     x8, Stack_handler(TMP)
  811.         ldr     TMP, Handler_parent(x8)
  812.         cbnz    TMP, 1b
  813.     /* Add current stack to the end */
  814.         ldr     x9, Caml_state(current_stack)
  815.         str     x9, Handler_parent(x8)
  816.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS x9, x0
  817.         mov     x0, x2
  818.         br      x3
  819. 2:      ADDRGLOBAL(ADDITIONAL_ARG, caml_raise_continuation_already_resumed)
  820.         b       G(caml_c_call)
  821.         CFI_ENDPROC
  822.         END_FUNCTION(caml_resume)

  824. /* Run a function on a new stack, then either
  825.    return the value or invoke exception handler */
  826. FUNCTION(caml_runstack)
  827. CFI_STARTPROC
  828.     /*  x0: fiber
  829.         x1: fun
  830.         x2: arg */
  831.         CFI_OFFSET(29, -16)
  832.         CFI_OFFSET(30, -8)
  833.         stp     x29, x30, [sp, -16]!
  834.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  835.         add     x29, sp, #0
  836.         sub     x0, x0, 1  /* x0 := Ptr_val(x0) */
  837.         ldr     x3, [x1]   /* code pointer */
  838.     /*  save old stack pointer and exception handler */
  839.         ldr     x8, Caml_state(current_stack) /* x8 := old stack */
  840.         mov     TMP, sp
  841.         str     TMP, Stack_sp(x8)
  842.         str     TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(x8)
  843.     /* Load new stack pointer and set parent */
  844.         ldr     TMP, Stack_handler(x0)
  845.         str     x8, Handler_parent(TMP)
  846.         str     x0, Caml_state(current_stack)
  847.         ldr     x9, Stack_sp(x0) /* x9 := sp of new stack */
  848.     /* Create an exception handler on the target stack
  849.        after 16byte DWARF & gc_regs block (which is unused here) */
  850.         sub     x9, x9, 32
  851.         adr     TMP, L(fiber_exn_handler)
  852.         str     TMP, [x9, 8]
  853.     /* link the previous exn_handler so that copying stacks works */
  854.         ldr     TMP, Stack_exception(x0)
  855.         str     TMP, [x9]
  856.         mov     TRAP_PTR, x9
  857.     /* Switch to the new stack */
  858.         mov     sp, x9
  859. #ifdef ASM_CFI_SUPPORTED
  860.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  861.         .cfi_escape DW_CFA_def_cfa_expression, 3+3+2,       \
  862.           DW_OP_breg + DW_REG_sp,                           \
  863.             16 /* exn */ +                                  \
  864.             8 /* gc_regs slot (unused) */ +                 \
  865.             8 /* C_STACK_SP for DWARF (unused) */           \
  866.             + Handler_parent_offset, DW_OP_deref,           \
  867.           DW_OP_plus_uconst, Stack_sp_offset, DW_OP_deref,  \
  868.           DW_OP_plus_uconst, 16 /* fp + ret addr */
  869. #endif
  870.     /* Call the function on the new stack */
  871.         mov     x0, x2
  872.         blr     x3
  873. L(frame_runstack):
  874.         add     x8, sp, 32 /* x8 := stack_handler */
  875.         ldr     x19, Handler_value(x8) /* saved across C call */
  876. 1:
  877.         mov     x20, x0     /* save return across C call */
  878.         ldr     x0, Caml_state(current_stack) /* arg to caml_free_stack */
  879.     /* restore parent stack and exn_handler into Caml_state */
  880.         ldr     TMP, Handler_parent(x8)
  881.         str     TMP, Caml_state(current_stack)
  882.         ldr     TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(TMP)
  883.         str     TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  884.     /* free old stack by switching directly to c_stack;
  885.        is a no-alloc call */
  886.         ldr     x21, Stack_sp(TMP) /* saved across C call */
  887.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  888.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  889.         CFI_DEF_CFA_REGISTER(DW_REG_x21)
  890.         ldr     TMP, Caml_state(c_stack)
  891.         mov     sp, TMP
  892.         bl      G(caml_free_stack)
  893.     /* switch directly to parent stack with correct return */
  894.         mov     x0, x20
  895.         mov     x1, x19
  896.         mov     sp, x21
  897.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  898.         ldr     TMP, [x19]  /* code pointer */
  899.     /* Invoke handle_value (or handle_exn) */
  900.         ldp     x29, x30, [sp], 16
  901.         CFI_ADJUST(-16)
  902.         br      TMP
  903. L(fiber_exn_handler):
  904.         add     x8, sp, 16  /* x8 := stack_handler */
  905.         ldr     x19, Handler_exception(x8)
  906.         b       1b
  907.         CFI_ENDPROC
  908.         END_FUNCTION(caml_runstack)

  910. FUNCTION(caml_ml_array_bound_error)
  911.         CFI_STARTPROC
  912.     /* Load address of [caml_array_bound_error_asm] in ADDITIONAL_ARG */
  913.         ADDRGLOBAL(ADDITIONAL_ARG, caml_array_bound_error_asm)
  914.     /* Call that function */
  915.         b       G(caml_c_call)
  916.         CFI_ENDPROC
  917.         END_FUNCTION(caml_ml_array_bound_error)

  919.          TEXT_SECTION(caml_system__code_end)
  920.         .globl  G(caml_system__code_end)
  921. G(caml_system__code_end):

  923. /* GC roots for callback */

  925. OBJECT(caml_system.frametable)
  926.         .quad   2               /* two descriptors */
  927.         .quad   L(caml_retaddr) /* return address into callback */
  928.         .short  -1              /* negative frame size => use callback link */
  929.         .short  0               /* no roots */
  930.         .align  3
  931.         .quad   L(frame_runstack) /* return address into fiber handler */
  932.         .short  -1              /* negative frame size => use callback link */
  933.         .short  0               /* no roots here */
  934.         .align 3
  935.         END_OBJECT(caml_system.frametable)

  937. #if !defined(SYS_macosx)
  938. /* Mark stack as non-executable */
  939.         .section .note.GNU-stack,"",%progbits
  940. #endif
